@@GHISTORY@@W

The psionicist tradition has the most contested origin in the world. The
Spirebound Conclave's Pale Ledger faction — practitioners of spirit imprinting
and iterative memory extraction — are the most documented predecessors, though
psionicists themselves rarely claim that lineage openly. A parallel thread runs
through the Void Citadel's recurrence technology, which weaponized testimony
replay to dissolve resistance by collapsing the distinction between memory and
present experience. Whatever the genealogy, the practical discipline emerged in
eras when the most dangerous institutions were those that controlled what could
be known and remembered: the Kel'Shadra witness order, the Great Pyramid's
Seal College, the Conclave's cognitive programs. Psionicists are the inheritors
of that contested space — minds trained to reach past surface resistance into
the architecture of will itself, turning thought into force the way earlier
institutions turned record-keeping into control.

@@GPSIONICIST@@W

Psionicists turn thought into weapon and ward, overwhelming enemies through
focused will, mental pressure, and disciplined control of unseen force.

